      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">8/2/83 ¶  ¶ This day, dear Sir Joseph, I was greatly pleased to receive the finishing part of the third volume of your important "Flora of British India," ¶ J.Hooker (1875-97). ¶  ¶ the value of which...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">83.02.08</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1882-90, ff. 50-1.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">8/2/83</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This day, dear Sir Joseph, I was greatly pleased to receive the finishing part of the third volume of your important "Flora of British India,"<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Hooker (1875-97).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the value of which cannot be overrated.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In casting a glance on the pages I notice, that you maintain the name<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Lysimachia</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Javanica</hi>
               </seg>. Allow me, to draw your attention to the appendix, written by me for Campbell's New Hebrides in 1873.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B73.07.02.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Receiving Lysimachia decurrens from Java then, therefore from the very place, where the Forsters obtained their plant, I enquired into the synonymy, and was able from authentic specimens to refer L. Javanica, L. multiflora and L. Sinica <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to L. decurrens. This I mentioned to Dr Hance at the time, who received also "Campbell's New Hebrides," and hence it was, that he distributed the plant under its oldest name. An insignificant publication, such as my contribution to the little work above named, is so easily overlooked, that it is not surprising, that you missed the reference to the first name.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>An other item of some interest to you for the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">genera</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862-83).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>will be, that Helmholtzia is likely endemic Australian only. I have just received from M.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>de la<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Camera<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>i.e. de la<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Camara.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the H. glaberrima, who found it on the summit of the White-cap Mountain near the Tweed-River.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Night-cap Range, NSW?</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I send a short note now on this subject to Caruel for his giornale<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B83.04.02.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>as he is interested in this plant.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I mentioned to you, so soon as I got the plate 6056 of the Bot. Magazine,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Philydrum glaberrimum</seg>, illustrated in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>J.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Hooker (1865-1904</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">)</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">,</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>vol. 99, t. 6056 (published<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1 September 1873).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>that the plant belonged to the genus Helmholtzia, as defined in 1866,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn7" n="8">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M erected<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Helmholtzia</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">H. acorifolia</seg>) in B66.12.04, pp. 202-3.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and that it may be a glabrous form of H.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>acorifolia.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn8" n="9">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M to J. Hooker, 1 December 1873<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 73-12-01b).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>In reply you wrote, that you had asked Prof. Oliver, to see, whether the plant occurred in the "fragmenta," but that he had missed to note it;<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn9" n="10">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>my Census<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn10" n="11">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B83.03.04.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>will facilitate all references to that work in future.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Helmholtzia acorifolia</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Helmholtzia glaberrima</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Lysimachia decurrens</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Lysimachia Javanica</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Lysimachia multiflora</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Lysimachia Sinica</p>
         </div>
      </body>
